=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Multichannel-Expansion_ex8 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_bright pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 148 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally dense.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_bright
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: dense
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 148.1098
  harmonic_decay_rate: -5.2402
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5467
  pitch_clarity: 171.0215
  inharmonicity: 0.1764
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -11.4216
  resonance_freq: 258.3984

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Multichannel Expansion Example 8
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Multichannel-Expansion.html
// Tags: Multichannel-Expansion, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 8 ---
{ Saw.ar([100,250]) * [0.5,0.8] }.play;
{ Saw.ar(LFNoise1.kr(1).range(0,100) + [100,250]) }.play;
